<subSubSection pageId="10" pageNumber="11" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,950,1299]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1131,1155]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has perhaps the most distinctive and easily identified sculpture of any of the South Pacific 
<taxonomicName box="[236,370,1166,1190]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[236,370,1166,1190]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Leptochiton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp., with around 
<number box="[580,608,1166,1190]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="50.0">50</number>
well-separated longitudinal rows of round granules on the central area of intermediate valves and radiating chains of flatter granules on the lateral areas (see 
<bibRefCitation author="Kaas" box="[1109,1385,1202,1226]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of Living Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora), Volume 1. Order Neoloricata, Lepidopleurina. Backhuys, Leiden, 240 pp." type="book" year="1985">
Kaas &amp; Van Belle 
<number box="[1325,1385,1202,1226]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1985.0">1985</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 
<number box="[151,183,1238,1262]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="54.0">54</number>
). 
<bibRefCitation box="[202,484,1238,1262]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" refString="Kaas, P. &amp; Van Belle, R. A. (1985) Monograph of Living Chitons (Mollusca: Polyplacophora), Volume 1. Order Neoloricata, Lepidopleurina. Backhuys, Leiden, 240 pp." type="book">
Kaas &amp; Van Belle (
<number box="[418,476,1238,1262]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="1985.0">1985</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
erroneously reported that 
<taxonomicName box="[779,879,1238,1263]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="foresti">
<emphasis box="[779,879,1238,1263]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">L. foresti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has 
<number box="[930,1000,1238,1262]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="17.0" valueMax="18.0" valueMin="16.0">16–18</number>
gills per side. The species consistently has 
<number box="[195,223,1274,1298]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11" value="10.0">10</number>
gills per side in adult specimens, confirmed here by re-examination of the 
<typeStatus box="[1063,1111,1275,1299]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">type</typeStatus>
series.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
